%text
% \[ \vert\sin x\vert = \begin{cases}
\sin x, \, x\in \left[0,\frac\pi{2} \right] \\ - \left(\sin \left(-x \right) \right) = \sin x,\, x\in \left(-\frac\pi{2},0 \right) \end{cases} \] %text In other words, $f(x) = f(-x)$. And hence, $f(x) = \vert\sin x\vert$ is an \underline\text{even function} And we know that for even functions \[ \quad \int_{-a}^a f(x)\cdot dx = 2\int_0^a f(x)\cdot dx \] And therefore, % \begin{align}
\intga \vert\sin x\vert\cdot dx &= \intgb \vert\sin x\vert\cdot dx \\ &= \intgb \sin x\cdot dx \\ &= 2\left[-\cos x \right]_0^{\frac\pi{2}} = 2 \end{align} %text %
